// Elite mode ("Nhím Tinh Hoa") — the HARDEST tier, the very top of the app.
// DIFFICULTY TARGET: a BIG jump above Master ("Nhím Cao Thủ"). Someone flipping
// Chill -> Master -> Elite must instantly see each step up.
//   Chill  = Grade-2 vocab, one direct step, picture usually gives the answer.
//   Master = 1-2 steps, near-miss distractors, still Grade-2 vocabulary.
//   Elite  = 3-4 step reasoning (sometimes conditional), multi-blank fills where
//            each blank needs a DIFFERENT rule, chained/two-layer analogies,
//            "only ONE sentence is correct" with subtle differences, odd-one-out
//            with a decoy grouping ruled out by an instruction, counting across
//            TWO sentences, rule-application, and meta-reasoning ("why is it
//            right", "which pair is WRONG"). Vocabulary is deliberately RICH:
//            astonished, magnificent, reluctant, ferocious, delicate, feeble,
//            cunning, drought, fragrant, translucent, peculiar, ancient, vast,
//            timid, courageous, enormous, furious, transparent... — real,
//            learnable English that stretches a strong young reader.
//   Almost ZERO picture hints (img only very rarely).
// IMPORTANT: no item, distractor set, or "trick" here is reused from the Chill or
// Master banks, and every item is written to read clearly HARDER than Master.
// s:true = Scholar question (2 marks). Correct answer is written first (a:0) for
// authoring convenience; options are shuffled when shown.
window.APP_DATA.elite = {
  topics: {

    "words": [
      { q: "'Furious' is a STRONGER form of 'angry', just as 'delighted' is a stronger form of 'glad'.\nSo which word is the strongest form of 'big'?", o: ["enormous", "little", "wide", "heavy"], a: 0, s: true },
      { q: "The prefix 'un-' means 'not' and the ending '-ful' means 'full of'.\nSo the word 'ungrateful' describes someone who is ________.", o: ["not full of thanks", "very thankful", "full of gifts", "thankful again"], a: 0, s: true },
