      { q: "'Ancient' means very, very old, and 'vast' means very, very large.\nSo an 'ancient, vast desert' is one that is ________.", o: ["old and huge", "new and tiny", "young and narrow", "cold and small"], a: 0 },
      { q: "Three of these words mean 'shy'. One means the OPPOSITE.\nWhich word means the OPPOSITE of shy?", o: ["bold", "timid", "fearful", "bashful"], a: 0, s: true },
      { q: "A long time with NO rain is called a 'drought'.\nSo during a drought, rivers and wells most likely become ________.", o: ["dry", "deeper", "faster", "colder"], a: 0 },
      { q: "'Glass' lets ALL light through, so it is 'transparent'. Thin paper lets only SOME light through.\nSo thin paper is best called ________.", o: ["translucent", "transparent", "solid", "hollow"], a: 0, s: true },
      { q: "Fill BOTH blanks so the sentence makes sense.\n'The ________ old bridge was so ________ that it swayed in the wind.'", o: ["ancient - feeble", "modern - sturdy", "new - strong", "young - solid"], a: 0, s: true },
      { q: "Only ONE spelling is correct.", o: ["magnificent", "magnifisent", "magnificant", "magnifecent"], a: 0 },
      { q: "'Peculiar' means strange or odd.\nWhich word means the OPPOSITE of peculiar?", o: ["ordinary", "unusual", "curious", "rare"], a: 0, s: true },
      { q: "A 'fragrant' flower smells lovely. A 'delicate' vase breaks easily.\nSo a 'fragrant, delicate rose' is one that ________.", o: ["smells sweet and breaks easily", "has no smell and is very tough", "is loud and heavy", "tastes bad and is strong"], a: 0 },
